The arbitration board or, if only one arbitrator is appointed, the arbitrator may, among other things:
Require that each party to the controversy submit a written statement of its contention to the board and send a copy of the statement to the other party;
Make investigations, inspections, and examinations;
Take, receive, and keep a permanent record of testimony and other evidence;
Hold hearings after notice to the parties in interest; and
Adopt rules and regulations for the conduct of the arbitration proceedings.
